<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 2:37AM MDT  by NWS Aberdeen</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Edmunds,
southern Brown, northeastern Faulk and northwestern Spink Counties
through 415 AM CDT...
At 337 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mellette, or 19 miles north of Redfield, moving north at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Warner around 350 AM CDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Aberdeen and Bath.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
